Rating: 4
I made this recipe based on the great reviews and I ideally wanted something I could make ahead of time. The previous reviews were very helpful - I too made the full recipe but split it into two portions - one full half to serve 3 days later and then split the other half between three ramekins that I have in the freezer. Additional tips that I would add are: 1) I find cream cheese traditionally hard to mix so I put the cream cheese and butter mixture in the microwave on defrost for just a very short period to soften it slightly and this allowed me to use the electrice beaters to easily blend them; 2) I did not have any problem layering the layers as I too put the dish into the freezer just for a few minutes btwn layers; 3) I used prepared pesto - amount wise I believe my jar was somewhere around 170-198 mls - let the jar stand and POUR OFF the oil that rises to the top like another reviewer suggested; 4) to serve, I was not sure how "firm" the torta would be right out of the fridge so I brought it out about 45-60 mins before serving it -probably 30 mins would be adequate; 5) I served it with sour dough baguette slices which was firm enough I didn't toast the slices; 6) For WINE we served a New Zealand Saugvignon Blanc which went nicely.

