As I was making this recipe, I swore I would never make it again because it was such a pain! The cream cheese and butter layer seemed to be the most difficult one to spread, even after trying the suggestions of previous reviewers. I had a sinkful of dishes and was getting very annoyed by the whole time consuming process. But when I unmolded the torta I was very impressed by its appearance, even though my layers were not perfect. Then I heard the ooo's and ah's from everyone who was eating it, and tasted it myself and all the hassle of making it just seemed to go away. It is absolutely delicious!

Rating: 4
Personally, I think provolone would be too firm, compared with the softness of the other layers. I admit I'm not a perfectionist, but I've made this many times, and the layers have always looked fine in the end. Don't stress out about it. The flavor is fantastic, the colors are festive, and this is as close to a guaranteed hit as one can get. In fact, I'm starting to prep it tonight for Christmas Eve. Definitely a laminate-worthy recipe.

