Rating: 3
Have made this twice and it has always been successful. I find it difficult though to spread the layers and not have them smush together. I've solved that by plopping down small spoonfuls of each layer and then gently merging them with a knife. It certainly looks nice, but it picks up the wrinkles from the plastic wrap and the layers certainly do not come out as even as in the photograph. But it tastes nice.

Rating: 4
This is a show-stopping crowd pleaser that is worth the time (I'd allow 2 hours) it takes to make. I added 4 oz. feta to the cream cheese/butter mixture, along with 1/2 tsp white pepper to give it a little kick. Whoever suggested early on in the reviews to use a spoon dipped in hot water (and dried) to smooth the layers is a genius, it works like a charm! I used sandwich-size zip-loc bags as piping bags for the pesto and tomato layers and that was easier than trying to spoon it on. Also put the pan in the freezer about 5 minutes between layers to harden it a little. Wrapped well, this will freeze up to a month ahead.

