Rating: 4
This has become one of my party staples. I love to make it -- and people just rave about it. Having made it at least 10 times, I think the best way to do the layers is by having TRULY room temperature cream cheese -- the softer it is, the easier it will be to spread. I use the plastic bags with an end snipped off and a hot spoon lightly covered with cooking spray. Very simple. I've gotten it down to where the whole thing takes about 30 minutes. And I like to experiment with different dishes -- sometimes a round souffle dish, once a cube-shaped vase! Fun, tasty and beautiful...

