Rating: 4
All my guests loved this torta! I had a bit of a problem with spreading my layers (except the basil one) they were a bit thick, maybe because I had the windows open and it was cold out, so it really wasn't room temperature. Anyway, here's a tip if you have this problem too (besides closing the windows), drop tablespoons full of whatever layer you're working with, in little clumps all over the surface. This way, you don't have to try and spread from one central location. I found the basil layer "looser", so when I put my next layer down, it sort of smeared together, until I came up with the clumps thing.

