An easier, chunky version of this is to use store bought pesto and to leave the sun-dried tomatoes julienned instead of processing them (measure with the oil drained). Increase the cream cheese and butter to 4 - 8oz pkgs and 1 cup. Increase the pinenuts to 1 c. Toast them, then sprinkle heavily over the pesto layers and use to garnish on top.

