Rating: 4
This was a BIG hit! Everyone loved it. I simplified the recipe as follows: Since cream cheese comes in 8 oz. packages, I used 4 oz (1/2 a pkg) for each of the pesto and sundried tomatoes. I used 2 pkgs (16 oz total) with 1/2 cup butter (1stick). That way I didn't have odd pieces of butter or cream cheese left over and much easier to measure. My local market sells their own pesto, both in traditional basil and in sun-dried tomato. I used about 1/2 cup of each. That made the mixing easy. I didn't have any fresh basil and sprinkled chopped walnuts on top. It was great!

